	<!-- House Soren -->
	<FactionDef ParentName="DankPyon_NobleHouseFactionBase">
		<defName>DankPyon_NobleHouseCivil2</defName>
		<label>civil noble house</label>
		<description>War is a profitable endeavor, much so, that trading and haggling is as relentlessly ferocious as winning a battle. House Soren is notoriously recognized to be the masters of the trade, cunningly closing each profitable bargain. Many of their acquisitions are gained by honest trading but also through deceit, bribery, and extortion. Their towns are filled with riches as the house resides in their decadent castles, whilst pot-bellied peasants litter the streets.

House Soren's influence stretches far and wide, with their merchant fleets dominating the seas and their caravans threading through the most dangerous routes. They possess a network of spies and informants, ensuring they are always a step ahead of their rivals. The halls of their castles are adorned with treasures from distant lands, a testament to their vast wealth and far-reaching connections.

Once subjugated under the oppressive rule of the shattered empire, House Soren was among the first to seize the opportunity for independence when the empire's grip weakened. Their struggle for control over the other houses has been fierce, leveraging their economic prowess to tip the scales in their favor. They have successfully established themselves as a dominant force, exploiting the power vacuum left by the empire's collapse.</description>
